<p>Why the XScriptContext is used like this:</p>  <pre><code>oDoc = XSCRIPTCONTEXT.getDocument(); </code></pre>  <p>And can't be used like all the other classes and objects:</p>  <pre><code>importClass(Packages.com.sun.star.script.provider.XScriptContext) oDoc = XScriptContext.getDocument(); </code></pre>  <p>What is so special about this object? Why is it defined the way it is?</p>